      • printSortPrint

        public static void printSortPrint(TenXer[] sample)
        Accepts an array of TenXers. First, prints the names in the order they were passed in. Second, it sorts the array. Finally, it prints the names in the order they are sorted You Do not need to have Sorting.java properly implented for this.
        Parameters:
        sample - Array of TenXer's to visualize, sort, then visualize.

      • getRuntime

        public static long getRuntime(int n,
                              java.lang.String sortingAlgorithm)
        Calculates the runtime for running a Insertion or Merge sort over a given input n with TenXer objects.
        Parameters:
        n - Number of TenXers to sort
        sortingAlgorithm - 'Insertion' or 'Merge' denoting their respective algorithms
        Returns:
        long Runtime to sort n elements by the chosen sorting algorithm. -1 if n is less than or equal to 0.
